      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHOULD BE QUEEN (7) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing seventh (23.35) at Warrnambool in a Bottom Up - Maiden. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. COLLINDA NEL (6) drew a middle box and finished towards the tailenders on debut at this track over 400m (23.81). This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. YELLOW SAPPHIRE (3) is a handily bred pup making her debut without a trial. Can kick off with a good run. MYSTERY NELL (8) is a Cheryl Pirani-trained newcomer by Aussie Secret out of What A Surprise. Start all important and will need some luck getting across from the wide draw. Can sneak into the frame with the right run.",
